snippet.textDisplay:
Payton Manning played his worst season ever in his last year with the Broncos. And yet he still beat out Osweiler and won a super bowl not because of his physical prowess but because of his football IQ. Tom Brady is in the same situation, except his body hasnt broken down as quickly as Mannings did.


Raiders, Chargers, Dolphins, Buccs, Bengals, Redskins, Jaguares, Panthers all need or looking for a QB. (Gruden isnt happy unless he has 10 QB on the roster and the only reason I listed the raiders.) And if the Titans is a possible spot for Brady, why not the Vikings? They are a QB away from reaching the SB. Cousins isnt the answer especially if he wasnt able to do it with all the offensive weapons he had.
